# Offer Letter — AI Intern

Date: [Date]

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you the position of AI Intern at Omninuera. This letter summarizes the key terms of your internship. Please review and confirm your acceptance by signing and returning a copy.

## Position and Reporting
- **Role:** AI Intern  
- **Reporting to:** [Reporting Manager]  
- **Start Date:** [Start Date]  
- **Duration:** 3 months (fixed-term internship)  
- **Work location:** Completely remote. You will be based in Bengaluru and are expected to work remotely from that location.

## Compensation and Payment Schedule
- **Stipend:** INR 10,000 per month (paid as a stipend).  
- **Payment schedule:** Stipend will be paid monthly, within 7 business days after the end of each month, subject to submission of any required timesheets or reports.  
- **Taxes and deductions:** Any statutory taxes or other lawful deductions will be applied as required by law.

## Working Hours and Schedule
- **Expected hours:** Approximately 20–30 hours per week, with a flexible remote schedule to be agreed with your Reporting Manager.  
- **Core hours:** You may be asked to be available for meetings during mutually agreed core hours; your Reporting Manager will confirm these.  
- **Timesheets:** You may be required to submit weekly or monthly timesheets or progress reports as determined by your Reporting Manager.

## Leave and Benefits
- Public holidays observed by Omninuera will be communicated in advance.  
- **Sick leave:** Up to 2 days of paid sick leave during the internship, subject to notification and, where reasonable, medical certification.  
- **Other benefits:** This is an internship role. You are not eligible for full-time employee benefits (such as provident fund, health insurance, or paid annual leave) unless explicitly stated in writing.

## Probation and Termination
- **Probation/Assessment:** The internship includes an initial assessment period during the first two weeks to ensure a satisfactory fit; continued participation is subject to performance and mutual agreement.  
- **Termination by either party:** Either you or Omninuera may terminate the internship with 7 calendar days' written notice.  
- **Immediate termination for cause:** Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to breach of confidentiality, misconduct, gross negligence, or material violation of company policies.  
- **Suspension:** Omninuera may suspend your duties pending an investigation into alleged misconduct; suspension may be with or without stipend as determined by Omninuera in accordance with applicable law.

## Confidentiality
- You agree to maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera's confidential information during and after the internship.  
- Confidential information includes business plans, code, models, datasets, proprietary processes, client information, and all non-public information.  
- You must not disclose or use such information except as necessary to perform your duties and with prior written consent.

## Intellectual Property (IP) and Assignment
- Any inventions, designs, code, models, datasets, documentation, or other work product (collectively "Work Product") that you create, develop, or contribute to during the internship and which relate to Omninuera's business or result from your use of Omninuera resources are the exclusive property of Omninuera.  
- You hereby assign (and agree to assign) to Omninuera all rights, title, and interest in such Work Product and agree to execute any documents reasonably necessary to effectuate this assignment.  
- You represent that any pre-existing materials you incorporate into Work Product are identified in writing and that you have the right to license or assign such materials.

## Return of Property
- Upon termination or completion of the internship, you must promptly return or securely delete all company property and confidential information in your possession.

## Compliance with Company Policies
- Your internship is subject to Omninuera's policies, including but not limited to IT, data protection, acceptable use, and code of conduct policies. You must comply with all applicable policies as provided.

## Background Checks and Eligibility
- This offer is conditional on satisfactory verification of your eligibility to intern (identity, right to work, references, and any background checks that Omninuera deems necessary).

## No Guarantee of Employment
- This internship does not create a contract of employment for any specific duration beyond the stated period, nor does it guarantee any future employment. Any offer of employment would be at Omninuera's sole discretion and subject to a separate employment agreement.

## Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign below and return a scanned copy to HR by email. This offer is valid until [Offer Expiry Date].

Sincerely,

[Name]  
[Title]  
Omninuera

Accepted and agreed:

